Author::::d33pf1x
DateTime::::2016-02-17T12:34:09Z
It's a Derbyshire tradition which is said to have its origins in the days of the plague. Many of the villages in Derbyshire were plague free and it was believe at the time that the wells providing the water were the reason, so the locals started decorating the wells and giving thanks for their plague free status.At least that's what they told us back in the Seventies when I was at school and it was well dressing season.



