Author::::Adrian Johnson
DateTime::::2016-02-17T12:27:32Z
Well-Dressing is alive and well every summer in C of E and RC Churches in Derbyshire ! I myself take part with my fellow- parishioners every year for a week in helping to pressing petals, bark, pepper-corns, and cloves, into a clay-covered sheet of plyboard overlaid with computer-generated diagram of whatever picture has been voted on by the parish for that year. The local Catholic school has a smaller, simpler flower picture done by the school children. The elaborate flower pictures are always placed by an ancient spring decorated with garlands; there is a procession and blessing each year of our well on the banks of the River Etherow; and then a luncheon and tea in a rented pavilion where every one enjoys the weather, rain or shine.



